1a:["$","tr","7",{"className":"border-b border-[#1E3A5F]/50 hover:bg-[#162440]/50 transition-colors","children":[["$","td","0",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"File Storage"}],["$","td","1",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"10 GB/user (Pro)"}],["$","td","2",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"1 TB/organization + SharePoint"}]]}]
1b:["$","tr","8",{"className":"border-b border-[#1E3A5F]/50 hover:bg-[#162440]/50 transition-colors","children":[["$","td","0",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Best For"}],["$","td","1",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Fast-moving teams prioritizing UX"}],["$","td","2",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Microsoft-centric enterprises"}]]}]
1c:["$","h2","20",{"className":"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight","children":"Messaging: Slack Leads, But Teams Is Catching Up"}]
1d:["$","h3","22",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-8 mb-3","children":"Slack's Advantage"}]
1e:["$","p","24",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["Slack's threading model is the gold standard for a reason. Conversations stay organized without cluttering the main channel. According to G2 user reviews, Slack scores 92% for ease of use — one reviewer from a SaaS company put it simply: \"Slack just feels like how chat should work. I never have to teach new hires how to use it.\""]}]
1f:["$","p","26",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["The search functionality is also superior. You can search by file type, sender, channel, date range, and even content within attached documents. A Capterra reviewer noted, \"I can find a message from two years ago in seconds. Teams search still feels like a Google search from 2010.\""]}]
20:["$","h3","28",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-8 mb-3","children":"Teams' Improvements"}]
21:["$","p","30",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["Microsoft has significantly improved its messaging experience. The new chat experience (rolled out in late 2025) reduced UI clutter, and threaded replies are now the default in channels. However, G2 data shows Teams still trails Slack on messaging satisfaction (84% vs 92%)."]}]
22:["$","p","32",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["Teams excels in structured scenarios — when a conversation needs to be linked to a specific file, task, or meeting, the deep Office 365 integration creates context that Slack can't match. One enterprise IT director told me: \"In Teams, every chat about a document is connected to the document itself. In Slack, it's just text.\""]}]
23:["$","p","34",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Winner for messaging: Slack"}]," — but the gap is narrowing."]}]
24:["$","h2","36",{"className":"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight","children":"Video Conferencing: Teams Dominates"}]
25:["$","p","38",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["This is where the comparison gets lopsided. Slack's native video is limited to Huddle Calls (lightweight audio/video for up to 50 people) and Slack Connect calls. For serious video conferencing, Slack users typically add Zoom ($15.99/user/month) or Google Meet."]}]
26:["$","p","40",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["Teams, by contrast, includes enterprise-grade video with breakout rooms (up to 50), live captions and transcription, background effects, Together Mode, and support for up to 1,000 participants (10,000 with webinar add-on). Microsoft's AI-powered noise suppression is industry-leading."]}]
27:["$","p","42",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["For remote teams that run daily standups, virtual all-hands, and client meetings, Teams has a clear edge."]}]
28:["$","p","44",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Winner for video: Microsoft Teams"}]," — by a wide margin."]}]
29:["$","h2","46",{"className":"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight","children":"Integrations: Different Ecosystems"}]
2a:["$","h3","48",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-8 mb-3","children":"Slack's App Directory"}]
2b:["$","p","50",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["Slack's App Directory offers 2,600+ integrations, and the platform's philosophy of \"integrate with everything\" means you'll find connectors for almost any SaaS tool. Key integrations include: Google Workspace, Salesforce, Jira, Asana, GitHub, and most CRM and project management tools."]}]
2c:["$","p","52",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["Slack uses Granular Permissions — you can control exactly what data each app can access. One security-conscious G2 reviewer noted: \"Slack's app permissions are more granular than Teams. I feel confident granting limited access.\""]}]
2d:["$","h3","54",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-8 mb-3","children":"Teams' Microsoft Ecosystem"}]
2e:["$","p","56",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["Teams integrates seamlessly with Office 365 — SharePoint, OneDrive, Planner, Power BI, Forms, and Dynamics 365 work as native experiences within Teams. For organizations already on the Microsoft stack, this integration is difficult to overstate."]}]
2f:["$","p","58",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["However, third-party integration is more limited (1,800+ apps vs Slack's 2,600+). According to G2 reviews, Teams scores 84% on integrations satisfaction compared to Slack's 90%."]}]
30:["$","p","60",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Winner for integrations: Slack"}]," — unless you're already deep in the Microsoft ecosystem."]}]
31:["$","h2","62",{"className":"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight","children":"AI Features: The 2026 Differentiator"}]
32:["$","h3","64",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-8 mb-3","children":"Slack AI"}]
33:["$","p","66",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["Slack AI ($10/user/month add-on) offers: channel recaps (AI-generated summaries of what you missed), search answers (ask questions in natural language), conversation summaries, and AI-powered writing assistance. Early adopters report saving 1-2 hours per week on information catch-up."]}]
34:["$","h3","68",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-8 mb-3","children":"Microsoft Copilot in Teams"}]
35:["$","p","70",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["Microsoft's Copilot ($30/user/month for Microsoft 365 Copilot) is more ambitious. It can: summarize meetings with action items, draft messages in your tone, catch you up on Teams chats and channel posts, and even analyze meeting sentiment. Copilot's advantage is context — it can pull data from across your M365 tenant (email, documents, meetings, chats) to provide insights."]}]
36:["$","p","72",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["Both AI tiers are powerful but expensive at scale. For a team of 500, Slack AI adds $60K/year while Copilot adds $180K/year."]}]
37:["$","p","74",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Winner for AI features: Microsoft Teams"}]," — Copilot's cross-app context gives it an edge, but at 3x the price."]}]
38:["$","h2","76",{"className":"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight","children":"Pricing Comparison"}]
39:["$","div","table-84",{"className":"overflow-x-auto mb-6","children":["$","table",null,{"className":"w-full text-sm border-collapse","children":[["$","thead",null,{"children":["$","tr",null,{"className":"bg-[#162440]","children":[["$","th","0",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-left text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-[#3B82F6] border-b border-[#1E3A5F]","children":"Plan"}],["$","th","1",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-left text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-[#3B82F6] border-b border-[#1E3A5F]","children":"Slack"}],["$","th","2",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-left text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-[#3B82F6] border-b border-[#1E3A5F]","children":"Teams"}]]}]}],["$","tbody",null,{"children":[["$","tr","0",{"className":"border-b border-[#1E3A5F]/50 hover:bg-[#162440]/50 transition-colors","children":[["$","td","0",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Free"}],["$","td","1",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Unlimited users, 90-day history, 10 apps"}],["$","td","2",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Unlimited users, unlimited chat, 60-min meetings"}]]}],["$","tr","1",{"className":"border-b border-[#1E3A5F]/50 hover:bg-[#162440]/50 transition-colors","children":[["$","td","0",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Starter"}],["$","td","1",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"$$8.75/user/mo (Pro)"}],["$","td","2",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"$$4/user/mo (M365 Business Basic)"}]]}],["$","tr","2",{"className":"border-b border-[#1E3A5F]/50 hover:bg-[#162440]/50 transition-colors","children":[["$","td","0",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Mid-tier"}],["$","td","1",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"$$15/user/mo (Business+)"}],["$","td","2",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"$$12.50/user/mo (M365 Business Standard)"}]]}],["$","tr","3",{"className":"border-b border-[#1E3A5F]/50 hover:bg-[#162440]/50 transition-colors","children":[["$","td","0",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Enterprise"}],["$","td","1",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Custom (Enterprise Grid)"}],["$","td","2",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"$$22/user/mo (E3) or Custom (E5)"}]]}]]}]]}]}]
3a:["$","p","85",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"The hidden cost of Slack:"}]," At scale, Slack Enterprise Grid can cost $50,000-500,000/year depending on user count and add-ons. Many organizations moving from Slack to Teams cite cost as the primary reason (source: G2 Switching Costs report)."]}]
3b:["$","p","87",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"The hidden cost of Teams:"}]," It's bundled with M365, which most enterprise organizations already pay for. If you're on M365 E3 ($32/user/month), Teams is essentially \"free\" from a budget perspective."]}]
3c:["$","h2","89",{"className":"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight","children":"What Real Users Say"}]
3d:["$","h3","91",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-8 mb-3","children":"Slack Users Say"}]
3e:["$","p","93",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["\"I've tried moving our team to Teams three times. Each time, they revolt within a week and demand Slack back. The UX is just better.\" — G2 review, Mid-market SaaS Director of Engineering"]}]
3f:["$","p","95",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["\"Slack's search saved us hours of investigation time when we needed to find a configuration conversation from six months ago.\" — Capterra review, Enterprise IT Manager"]}]
40:["$","h3","97",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-8 mb-3","children":"Teams Users Say"}]
41:["$","p","99",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["\"Once you're in the Microsoft ecosystem, Teams is the obvious choice. The integration with SharePoint, Planner, and Outlook makes collaboration seamless.\" — G2 review, Enterprise IT Director"]}]
42:["$","p","101",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["\"Teams has come a long way in the last two years. We switched from Slack in 2024 and our team barely noticed the difference.\" — TrustRadius review, Mid-market Ops Manager"]}]
43:["$","h2","103",{"className":"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight","children":"Verdict: Which Should You Choose?"}]
44:["$","h3","105",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-8 mb-3","children":"Choose Slack if:"}]
45:["$","p","107",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["✅ Your team values speed and UX above everything else"]}]
46:["$","p","108",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["✅ You rely on hundreds of integrations with non-Microsoft tools"]}]
47:["$","p","109",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["✅ Your organization is not heavily invested in the Microsoft ecosystem"]}]
48:["$","p","110",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["✅ You need best-in-class messaging and search"]}]
49:["$","p","111",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["✅ Your team is under 500 users (Slack is most cost-effective at this scale)"]}]
4a:["$","h3","113",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-8 mb-3","children":"Choose Microsoft Teams if:"}]
4b:["$","p","115",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["✅ Your organization is already on Microsoft 365 (E3/E5)"]}]
4c:["$","p","116",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["✅ Video conferencing quality and reliability are critical"]}]
4d:["$","p","117",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["✅ You need deep integration with SharePoint, OneDrive, and Office apps"]}]
4e:["$","p","118",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["✅ Your organization has 1,000+ users (Teams scales more cost-effectively)"]}]
4f:["$","p","119",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["✅ Compliance and retention policies are strict requirements"]}]
50:["$","h3","121",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-8 mb-3","children":"My Personal Take"}]
51:["$","p","123",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["If I were building a startup today, I'd start with Slack. It's simply a better messaging tool, and at small scale the cost difference is negligible."]}]
52:["$","p","125",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["If I were a CIO at a 5,000-person enterprise already on Microsoft 365, I'd choose Teams. The cost savings at scale are significant ($200K-500K/year), the video capabilities are superior, and the integration depth with Office 365 creates real productivity advantages that Slack can't match."]}]
53:["$","p","127",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"The bottom line:"}]," There's no wrong answer — but there's a wrong answer for your specific situation. Slack is better at messaging and integrations. Teams is better at video and enterprise integration. Choose based on your priorities, not the hype."]}]
54:["$","p","129",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["*Sources: G2 Slack vs Microsoft Teams comparisons (Spring 2026), Capterra user reviews (2026), TrustRadius verified reviews (2026). Pricing data from official vendor websites as of May 2026.*"]}]
